CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 21, 1944, pg. 13, reads: "PITTSBURGH HONORS LENA HORNE - After her socko performance in Pittsburgh, Lena is shown at the station with her father, Teddy Horne (left) and her accompanist, Horace Henderson, as they entrained for Chicago ... then to Hollywood."
TitMainTitle: Louis Jones and Lena Horne standing in Pittsburgh train station
